added.title: BBSFBDAY!
added.description: Beast Boy agrees to share his birthday with Starfire after learning she's never had one on Earth.

added.title: BBCYFSHIPBDAY
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg celebrate the birthday of their friendship.

added.title: Beast Girl
added.description: As the Titans deal with Madame Rouge, Beast Boy is excited to meet his female counterpart Beast Girl.

added.title: Flashback Part 1
added.description: A flashback reveals how Robin formed the Teen Titans.

added.title: Flashback Part 2
added.description: A flashback reveals how Robin changed from mild-mannered sidekick to quick-tempered leader.

added.title: Bro-Pocalypse
added.description: When the male Titans are injured, Raven and Starfire must become bros to stop the Bropocalypse.

added.title: Dignity of Teeth
added.description: When Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, against Raven's advice the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.

added.title: Hey You, Don't Forget About Me in Your Memory
added.description: Robin convinces the Titans to go back to school with him so he can finally become the all-American class president-type he's dreamed of being.
Cyborg's real strength comes not from his robot parts, but from his favorite song.

added.title: BBBDay!
added.description: It's Beast Boy's birthday! But will the other Titans remember?

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppë, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Clown College
added.description: While tailgating at a State U. homecoming football game, Ben teams up with Grandpa Max's old college buddies to keep the crazy clown Zombozo from robbing the stadium blind at halftime.

added.title: Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max meet a family that appears to be a mirror image of them, but when Max goes off on a hike with their matriarch, Maxine, Ben is forced to babysit Simon Sez, a brat with a Billy Billions designed backpack  that turns him into a formidable robot.

added.title: Something I Ate
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max go on a tour of the impervious Fort Knox, but when Dr. Animo sicks a hungry ani-mutate on the Fort, Ben must stop it before it gobbles up the nation's monitory standard!

added.title: Steam is the Word
added.description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

added.title: The Beast Inside
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to "help", Ben must figure out if Tim is friend… or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Hole in 10
added.description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

added.title: Recipe for Disaster
added.description: During Chefapalooza in the Rocky Mountains, three famous chefs and infamous bad-guys, The Tri-Chefta, hunt down Wildvine in hopes of creating their most exotic dish to date.

added.title: Rustbucket RIP
added.description: During a tour of historic Oldeville Ben finds a rare Sumo Slammers card, but when Billy Billions comes to claim the same card Ben has to battle Billy's high-tech drones which have hijacked the Rust Bucket!

added.title: Freaky Gwen Ben
added.description: When Ben interferes with malicious magician Hex's quest for the earth-moving Titan Gloves at a swap meet, he inadvertently switches bodies with Gwen forcing him to walk a mile in her shoes… and vice-versa!

added.title: Ben 24hrs
added.description: When Ben (and Gwen!) attempt to stay up all night for Adrenaland, the only theme park open 24/7, he not only fails to utilize his alien powers to stay awake, but his "sleep-alien-ing" causes disaster after disaster that Gwen must fix before things get way out of hand.

added.title: Bright Lights, Black Hearts
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max stop by the graveyard set of Gwen's favorite TV show, The Unalivers, but when Ben discovers its lead, Michael Morningstar, is an energy vampire he goes alien to show the world the real star of the show: Heatblast.

added.title: Don't Laze Me, Bro
added.description: Ben and his arch-enemy Billy Billions clash in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park, LASER TOWN. But, when Billy inadvertently ignites a robot rebellion, and the lasers are set from tag to disintegrate, their childish game escalates into a full blown war! The two foes find that they must set aside their petty differences and team up in order to make it out alive, let alone save the day!

added.title: Don't Let the Bass Drop
added.description: Ben and Gwen are excited to attend an Earth Day EDM concert in Portland until the show is hijacked by the sound-manipulating baddy Lord Decibel who uses sound as a weapon to trash the planet.

added.title: Bad Penny
added.description: Ben is at the annual Big Bacon Pig Parade, but childhood friend Penny Heaven has met the family to ruin Ben's fun with her safety-obsessed self. While dodging Penny's overzealous safety precautions, Ben uncovers a plot by the Bug Brothers to steal helium from the parade balloons to rob banks with! Penny's badgering turns the heist into an accidental kidnapping so Ben must not only stop the robbery but save his least favorite safety monitor in the process.

added.title: Zombozo-Land
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max revisit their favorite amusement park, renovated and re-branded as AdrenaWORLD! Unfortunately, the new management is Zombozo and his trio of new henchmen! He's got a plan to hypnotize everyone in the park to form a criminal army. Ben has to set aside his desire to ride every ride in the park and make things right.

added.title: Forgeti
added.description: When Gwen drags Ben along on a hike in search of the legendary Forgeti, a yeti that makes people forget they ever saw it, Ben is dubious. But with Dr. Animo on the trail of the mythical beast as well, what looks like a hoax becomes a hero time adventure for the ages, if Ben can remember it ever happened.

added.title: Max to the Max
added.description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Cutting Corners
added.description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben is more interested in a marathon of his favorite cartoon show, "Xingo", but when Ben goes Upgrade to get a better signal, the titular Xingo leaps from his animated dimension to ours, bringing mad chaos with him!

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Need for Speed
added.description: Touring Yellowstone, Ben uncovers a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below the national park, but with a little help from Old Faithful, Overflow is able to douse LaGrange's dreams.

added.title: Omni-Tricked
added.description: Ben's vacation to Portland is cut short when he discovers an 11th alien while battling a Dr. Animo Mega-Creature. But when the fight leaves his Omnitrix on the fritz cycling through all 11 aliens, Max seeks help from an old friend to fix the Omnitrix as other dangerous forces seek it including a mysterious alien that's the same species as the 11th alien, Vilgax!

added.title: Four Arms AW1: The Overlordess Games
added.description: Survival is reserved for only the strongest of warriors on Khoros, where Tetramands prove their worth by staving off savage beasts of the wild and going head-to-head inside massive gladiatorial arenas.

added.title: Heatblast AW1: Extreme Season
added.description: At its molten core, Pyros is your typical planet-like star and home to the Pyronites. With rocky exteriors capable of handling these extreme conditions, observe our fiery friends as they pass the time by perfecting their pyrokinetic powers while hanging ten on the gnarliest rivers of lava.

added.title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
added.description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

added.title: Stinkfly AW2: The Sweet Smell of Survival
added.description: For the Lepidopterrans, putting food on the family table is never as simple as running out to the grocery store. Watch as their elite Sky Soldiers go mandible-to-mandible with fearsome Tongue Beetles in what's sure to be a hunger game for the ages!

added.title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
added.description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

added.title: Diamondhead AW1: Great Petropian Civil War Part 1
added.description: Petropia is a planet as breathtaking and indestructible as its crystalline inhabitants, the Petropians. Occupied by many factions, a civil war broke out between the Petropians and the war-like Subsapiens from below. Little did they know, a third faction, the Antrosapians, awaited with far more sinister intentions for the kingdom.

added.title: Shockrock AW2: Fulmanian Conquest
added.description: For the Fulmini, enough is just never enough. Traveling from planet to planet, draining worlds of their energy, this mighty race of conquerors must siphon energy from other planets in order to keep their own tapped-out planet spinning.

added.title: XLR8 AW1: Gauntlet of Gliders
added.description: Kinet, a planet dominated by electrical storms, is home to the lightning quick Kinecelerans! To combat the inclement weather, younglings must complete the Running of the Gauntlet, a most epic retrieval of the gliders worn on their feet. Traversing the desolate terrain at high speeds to reach the lair of a Kinet Molluscarx, the young ones must obtain the creature's precious pearl if they are to fulfill this Kineceleran rite of passage.

added.title: Wildvine AW2: The Worldtree
added.description: The Verda World Tree gives life to the entire ecosystem surrounding it, but like any organic matter, this magnificent specimen has a life cycle of its own. That's where the Florauna come in, herding wild Mushroars, gigantic pollen beetles, to fertilize the wilting tree in time for a blooming spring.

added.title: Four Arms AW2: The Warspear
added.description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

added.title: Diamondhead AW2: Great Petropian Civil War Part  2
added.description: The Petrosapien Civil War comes to a crucial turning point as the crystalline Petrosapiens make the hard choice to team up with their warring sub-surface cousins, the Subsapiens, to defeat the monstrous Antrosapiens that dwell near Petropia's dark planetary core.

added.title: Grey Matter AW1: The Archivists
added.description: Galvan Prime is home to not only the galaxy's greatest minds, but a DNA bank of every alien species in the cosmos, thus ensuring that the planet forever remains the center of DNA research for the entire universe.

added.title: Heatblast AW2: Cold Snap
added.description: Join the Pyronites as they ring in the holidays with a special tradition that would make even the most warm-blooded of visitors go crazy from the heat— racing to the top of Mount Helios, an active volcano!

added.title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
added.description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

added.title: Cannonbolt AW1: Beach Ballers
added.description: As the premiere vacation spot of the cosmos, Arburia is not only a sandy paradise but home to the Arburian Pelarotas. Twelve excruciatingly long hours of work and school stand between the spherical species and a day at the beach spent perfecting their cannonball!

added.title: Wildvine AW1: Wild Siders
added.description: Flors Verdana, green with vegetation, is as wild and abundant as the Florauna that inhabit it. Let's take a walk on the wild side as the plant-based aliens trade admiring the planet's lush beauty for the dangerous thrill of waking a sleeping giant.

added.title: Overflow AW2: Sentries of Cascareau
added.description: When the Cascan Pirates aren't plundering the depths of Cascareau for buried treasure, they're depositing their spoils into savings accounts at the Fort Knox of the high seas — a bank built atop an ever-drifting island of pontoon boats, guarded by telepathic Cephalopods, its vaults impenetrable to all but the most loyal customers.

added.title: Overflow AW1: The Pirates of Cascareau
added.description: The torrential surface of the water planet Cascareau forces us undersea, but luckily, this is where all the swashbuckling action is! Let's navigate the watery depths as the Cascans fend off fellow pirates & vicious Leviathans on their quest for a bounty of Serpent Glass, the raw material needed to construct their exoskeleton.

added.title: Upgrade AW1: Crisis on Galvan B
added.description: Once devoid of natural life, Galvan B. was upgraded seemingly overnight after a Galvan terraform experiment accidentally crashed into the moon's surface. Relive the birth of the Galvanic Mechamorphs as they rise from the impact site and terraform their surroundings into the lush techno-organic moon we see today.

added.title: Stinkfly AW1: The Silent Circle
added.description: The circle of life on Lepidopterra is a stinky yet harmonious effort for Lepidopterrans. The wildlife - with slime and toxic gas at their disposal - work together to maintain order on the bustling swamp planet.

added.title: How to Draw XLR8
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw XLR8.

added.title: How to Draw Upgrade
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Upgrade.

added.title: How to Draw Diamondhead
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Diamondhead.

added.title: How to Draw Cannonbolt
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Cannonbolt.

added.title: How to Draw Four Arms
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Four Arms.

added.title: How to Draw Wildvine
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Wildvine.

added.title: How to Draw Stinkfly
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Stinkfly.

added.title: How to Draw Overflow
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Overflow.

added.title: How to Draw Grey Matter
added.description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Grey Matter.

added.title: The Guy
added.description: Gumball and Darwin put Anais' new friend, Josh, through a series of tests, to see if he's good enough for their sister. However, when the boys' extreme methods start freaking Josh out, he questions whether being Anais's friend is worth the trouble. So Gumball and Darwin end up having to convince Josh to give Anais a second chance.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Compilation
added.description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

added.title: The Countdown
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are running late for school but need to arrive in time to avoid expulsion. Gumball and Darwin hit snooze too many times on their alarm clock and miss the school-bus. Miss Simian has threatened to expel them if they don't get to school on time. A mysterious clock appears showing exactly how long they have to get to school. When it looks like they aren't going to make it in time, they stop the clock which effects the space/time continuum.

added.title: The Triangle
added.description: Gumball is jealous when Darwin discovers a hidden musical talent, and he may not be the only one. Darwin joins the school marching band, and his tin-whistle talent lands him the solo. Gumball misses having his friend to goof off with and tries to get rehearsal cancelled. So when Darwin's whistle is sabotaged nobody believes Gumball is innocent. Gumball, meanwhile, sets out to find the true culprit, or there may be no encore.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: The Boombox
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent Beatbox message, but why won't he just speak English?!!

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.title: Gem Heist
added.description: The Gems try to pull of a heist.

added.title: Log Date 7 15 2
added.description: Steven sneaks a listen to a friend's audio diary.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Frybo
added.description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

added.title: Just Be a Pebble
added.description: KO eats a piece of new candy at Gar's that makes him giant.

added.title: Know Your Mom
added.description: KO wants to surprise Carol with a gift for Mother's Day, but doesn't know what to get her.

added.title: We've Got Fleas
added.description: When Mikayla, a new animalistic robot, attacks, KO, Rad, and Enid have to think outside the box to defeat her.

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: Lad & Logic
added.description: KO learns the story of how Mr. Logic came to the plaza.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
added.description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: Bonnibel Bubblegum
added.description: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

added.title: Seventeen
added.description: A mysterious knight crashes Finn's birthday bash and presents him with a dangerous gift.

added.title: Marcy & Hunson
added.description: Hunson Abadeer returns to Ooo to bond with his daughter Marceline, but will he be able to prove that he's changed his soul-sucking ways?

added.title: Blenanas
added.description: Finn's latest literary work is met with only derision so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

added.title: Jake the Starchild
added.description: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

added.title: The Ultimate Adventure: Come Along with Me
added.description: The fate of Ooo is revealed to two adventurers in the distant future. Princess Bubblegum gathers her allies while Finn searches for a way to prevent the coming Great Gum War.

added.title: Orb
added.description: The dreams of Finn, Jake, and BMO fall under the influence of a mysterious orb.

added.title: Abstract
added.description: As Jake goes through some personal changes, he's haunted by a sinister dream encounter with his brother Jermaine.

added.title: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
added.description: An unexpected critic shows up at Ice King's latest Fionna and Cake book reading.

added.title: Three Buckets
added.description: Finn and Fern's carefree visit to some old ruins turns disastrous.

added.title: I Remember You Music Video
added.description: Bringing you another Adventure Time slow jam, it's Marceline and Ice King.

added.title: Through the Years: Princess Bubblegum
added.description: From a tiny gumball, to ruler of the Candy Kingdom, and now a great Warrior Princess! Not to mention those fun outfits! Check out the evolution of Princess Bubblegum throughout 10 years of Adventure Time!

added.title: Founder's Song Music Video
added.description: Dr. Gross sings a song about how the islands were started.

added.title: Slow Dance with You Music Video
added.description: Marceline performs a new song at her solo concert!

added.title: Food Chain Music Video
added.description: Finn teaches us about how the food chain works, through song.

added.title: Through the Years: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake the Dog to Jake the Blue Alien... Winged... Dog? Whatever you call him now, there's no denying Jake is the master of shape-shifting, sage advice, and bacon pancakes! Watch Jake's transformation throughout 10 seasons of Adventure Time!

added.title: Dream of Love Music Video
added.description: Be prepared to be serenaded by the sweet, sweet sounds of Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig.

added.title: Simon and Marcy's Origin Story
added.description: 996 years ago, a man named Simon Petrikov met a little girl named Marceline at the end of the Great Mushroom War, and they became great friends.

added.title: Through the Years: Finn the Human
added.description: Adventurer. Hero. Puncher of buns. Finn has come a long way from Boom Boom Mountain! Watch Finn grow up throughout 10 years of Adventure Time!

added.title: Cool Bro Bots
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby confront robots.

added.title: Fries Night
added.description: Benson wants some french fries to overcome his depression.

added.title: Can You Ear Me Now?
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby offend some people.

added.title: The Lunch Club
added.description: Rigby ruins Maellard's fancy lunch, and now he or Benson has to write a letter of resignation.

added.title: Cat Videos
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get Benson to stop watching cat videos.

added.title: Sleep Cycle
added.description: After staying up for two straight nights watching a movie marathon, Mordecai and Rigby have to get their sleep cycle back on track.

added.title: Lift With Your Back
added.description: Rigby wants to prove to Mordecai that he can earn a paycheck from another job.

added.title: Format Wars II
added.description: The Discmasters have to end the Format Wars once and for all.

added.title: Gamers Never Say Die
